                            <comment id="85787" author="thomas.risberg" created="Tue, 4 Dec 2012 16:07:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Would it make sense to add CDI support for MongoClient injection? This could be then be similar to the JPA support.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="85857" author="phil-schneider" created="Thu, 6 Dec 2012 13:18:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think most developer expect from a database that a safe/write will fail e.g. when there is a duplicate key exception.&lt;br/&gt;
Fire and forget is what you not expect as default.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86062" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 23:23:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Thomas - wouldn&apos;t you rather want to inject &lt;tt&gt;MongoTemplate&lt;/tt&gt; instances to benefit from the mapping infrastructure?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="86063" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 12 Dec 2012 23:24:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Philipp - dependes on who &quot;you&quot; is actually. Mongo developers coming to Java usually do and it&apos;s what you find all over the reference docs as well. But I generally agree, that&apos;s why we have this ticket &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="89519" author="mers" created="Fri, 19 Apr 2013 08:11:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should probably get bumped to supporting the 2.11 driver, given the release of Mongo 2.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="94114" author="too_many_details2" created="Wed, 2 Oct 2013 03:31:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Its now October, so coming up to a year. I&apos;m looking at using Spring Data in a new project with the latest Mongo and its drivers. I&apos;m getting warnings about deprecated classes. MongoClient support should be done by now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="94117" author="olivergierke" created="Wed, 2 Oct 2013 03:53:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=too_many_details2&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;too_many_details2&quot;&gt;Rakesh Patel&lt;/a&gt; The reason there&apos;s not much activity on the ticket is, that - to get this to work in general - there&apos;s no need to change anything. If you extend &lt;tt&gt;AbstractMongoConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt;, implement the &lt;tt&gt;mongo()&lt;/tt&gt; method and configure and return a &lt;tt&gt;MongoClient&lt;/tt&gt; instance as you like.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ticket is still around as we definitely should provide XML support for this as well, but as we see more and more people using JavaConfig for their infrastructure configuration, the already existing config option through &lt;tt&gt;AbstractMongoConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt; seems to be just fine. I&apos;ll go ahead and make sure this get&apos;s more obvious in the reference documentation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does that make sense?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="94123" author="too_many_details2" created="Wed, 2 Oct 2013 05:47:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it does and better &apos;marketing&apos; of this information is definately worthwhile as it will save other peoples time and wrong impressions. I&apos;ve satisifed now as I use Java config too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="94124" author="mers" created="Wed, 2 Oct 2013 05:52:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was also under the impression that Spring Data MongoDB wouldn&apos;t work with MongoClient, IIRC because my integration tests had failed some six months ago and there were no updates on this issue. I just tested replacing Mongo with MongoClient using AbstractMongoConfiguration, against Mongo 2.2.x and the 2.11.3 driver, and my integration tests are working. Cheers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
